headline: AT&T Stock Jumps. Its Earnings Sent Investors a Better Signal.
summary: AT&T  stock was rising on Wednesday after the wireless carrier topped Wall Street’s earnings and revenue targets for the fourth quarter.  The move higher came after AT&T reported adjusted earnings of 52 cents a share, as revenue rose 3.6% from a year ago to $33.5 billion.  AT&T added 421,000 postpaid customers over the quarter, a touch below estimates.

headline: AT&T Rises On Q4 Earnings Beat, Solid Financial Guidance Through 2028
summary: AT&T stock climbed amid better-than-expected guidance for the next three years. Q4 earnings and revenue beat views but wireless adds missed.
